OL,3,CNorthern cities will 'remain poorly
OL,4,Cserved' by rail, Government advisers
OL,5,Cwarn
OL,7,FThe NIC said in its report: "The
OL,8,Fcommission's analysis suggests there
OL,9,Fare key corridors which will remain
OL,10,Fpoorly served, such as links from
OL,11,FBirmingham to Manchester and the North
OL,12,FWest."
OL,14,FSir John Armitt, who chairs the NIC,
OL,15,Fsaid: "A long-term plan is needed to
OL,16,Faddress the key connectivity, capacity
OL,17,Fand reliability issues on the rail
OL,18,Fnetwork in the North and the Midlands."
